Indices on child objects such as references for a GeneralGlyph seem to have a problem since the dimension is actually on the parent.  The following are sample validation errors for this:

1:Index math should be statically computable, meaning that it should only contain dimension ids or constant values but index Index [referencedAttribute=layout:glyph, arrayDimension=0] of object referenceGlyph [id=Glyph__rule0__substrate__V0, reference=null] is not statically computable.
2:Index math should not go out-of-bounds but index Index [referencedAttribute=layout:glyph, arrayDimension=0] of object referenceGlyph [id=Glyph__rule0__substrate__V0, reference=null] goes out-of-bounds.

Should make sure child objects can see dimensions ids of parent.

Chris


